news.title: Thane: Mhada now plans to make Kalwa affordable housing hub
news.para: Jitendra Awhad said the department was working out a plan to procure a disputed land belonging to a now defunct engineering company spread over 100 acres in Kalwa (east).

news.title: More irregularities tumble out of Bengaluru development body as raids resume
news.para: On Tuesday, the zonal offices at RT Nagar, Banashankari, Vijayanagar, and HSR Layout were raided. Innumerable documents were scanned and the raids are likely to continue for another couple of days, sources said.

news.title: IT department detects Rs 400 crore black income after raids on two NCR realtors
news.para: The Central Board of Direct Taxes (CBDT) said in a statement that the preliminary analysis of the seized data found that the groups were receiving part of the sale consideration in cash against the sale of flats and such cash is not recorded in the books of accounts.

news.title: Gaya civic body to install QR code in 70,000 houses
news.para: The GMC has recently secured top position among all urban local bodies in the state having population of less than 10 lakh in Swachh Survekshan 2021.

news.title: From Dec 1, most Greater Noida development body's dues can be cleared online
news.para: ​Offline payment, along with the online services, however, will be available to farmers, allottees of residential plots up to 200 square metres (sqm) and industrial plots up to 400 sqm, officials said.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC upholds share wise sale of houses in Chandigarh
news.para: “Fragmentation of a site/building has to entail an element of permanent severance. Mere construction of three floors on a private plot and utilisation of the same as independent units would not amount to fragmentation.

news.title: South Delhi civic body proposes to hike property tax by 2-5%
news.para: Residential, commercial and non-residential plots (of up to 150 sqm) are currently divided into three categories in the city -- A-B; C-E' and F-H categories.

news.title: Mumbai: Report on One Avighna Park fire calls for action against flat owner, audit agency
news.para: The report has called for action against the flat owner where the blaze erupted under Section 53 (1) of the MRTP Act, 1966, for carrying out unauthorised work in the premises, and also black listing of the agency that certified that the fire fighting systems were functioning.

news.title: Delhi: Allottees of Dwarka MIG flats in a fix
news.para: DDA had launched a housing scheme in January 2021. Among the 1,354 flats on offer, the 348 MIG flats in Dwarka 16-B turned out to be the most sought after.

news.title: Repco Home Finance invites applications for MD, CEO post
news.para: ​Promoted by Repco Bank, Repco Home Finance has invited candidates with minimum qualification of a postgraduate degree in any subject from a UGC recognised university on a full-time basis.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji in talks to raise up to $375 million via Dubai property sale
news.para: ​​Shapoorji Pallonji International (SPINT) is the global arm of Shapoorji Pallonji Engineering & Construction (SP E&C) for its construction operations outside of India. SPINT has successfully built hundreds of diversified landmark structures worldwide in various segments, including residential, commercial, industrial, healthcare, hospitality, educational and stadiums.

news.title: ED seizes Indian, foreign currencies, documents of investment in IREO raids
news.para: According to the Enforcement Directorate (ED), the raids covered "business premises of IREO Pvt. Ltd, IDM Reality Pvt. Ltd, Madeira Conbuild Pvt. Ltd, Global Estate and others."

news.title: Some bondholders of China's Kaisa Group tap adviser to help recover dues: Source
news.para: Kaisa, which has the most offshore debt of any Chinese developer after China Evergrande Group, has not paid coupons totalling over $59 million due on Nov. 11 and 12, with 30-day grace periods for both.

news.title: UK to make electric car charging points compulsory in new buildings
news.para: Prime Minister Boris Johnson told business leaders that he will legislate to compel charging points in new homes, supermarkets and workplaces in England, as part of his carbon-slashing plans.

news.title: NoBroker raises $210 million in Series E funding round
news.para: With this funding NoBroker has now become an  unicorn. This brings the total funding raised by NoBroker to USD $361 million till date.
